<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] An agreement on the utilization of $10 million of 
the $15 million loan Turkey has extended to Azerbaijan has been 
signed in Ankara. The agreement was signed by Azerbaijani 
Ambassador to Ankara Mehmet Nevruz Oglu and Bulent Ozgun, 
foreign economic relations director general for the Treasury and 
foreign trade. Ozgun said the loan will be used in the 
construction of a Foreign Relations Center to be established in 
Azerbaijan. 

